<html>

<head>

</head>

<body class='main-body'>
<% if current_user %>Hi, <%=current_user.name%> <% end %>
<h3>Welcome to the FRED® Data Viewer!</h3>

<p>Please choose a dataset from the dropdown menu below, or browse through the database using the navigation links at the top of the page.</p>

<div>
  <form id='select_data' method='post' action='/'>
    <select name='dataset_code' class="dropdown">
      <option value='UNRATE'>Civilian Unemployment Rate</option>
      <option value='DGS10'>10-Year Treasury Constant Maturity Rate</option>
      <option value='CPIAUCSL'>Consumer Price Index for All Urban Consumers: All Items</option>
      <option value='GDPC1'>Real Gross Domestic Product</option>
      <option value='U6RATENSA'>Total unemployed, plus all marginally attached workers plus total employed part time for economic reasons</option>
    </select>
    <input type='submit' value='Submit'>
  </form>
</div>
<hr>
<div>
    <h3>Sign Up</h3>

  <form id="sign-up" method="post" action="/sign_up">
    <label class="label" for="name">Name</label>
    <input type="text" name="name" placeholder="e.g., joe" >
    <br>

    <label class="label" for="email">Email</label>
    <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="e.g., me@example.com" >
    <br>

    <label class="label" for="password">Password</label>
    <input type="password" name="password" placeholder="8 or more characters">
    <br>

    <div class="submit"><input type="submit" value="Sign Up"></div>
  </form>

</div>




<p>This application was built using the <a href="http://api.stlouisfed.org/docs/fred/">FRED® API</a>, which allows users to access the FRED (Federal Reserve Economic Data) and ALFRED (Archival Federal Reserve Economic Data) databases hosted by the <a href="http://research.stlouisfed.org/">Economic Research Division</a> of the <a href="http://stlouisfed.org/">Federal Reserve Bank of St. Louis</a>.</p>

<p>This tool allows users to view graphs for popular datasets, as well as find up to date information on the sources of information available through FRED.</p>

</body>
</html>